5. A method of detecting lymphoma in a person, comprising:
a. obtaining a plasma sample from the person;
b. measuring the level of at least one protein listed in Table S3 in the plasma sample;
c. comparing the level of the at least one protein in the plasma sample with the level in a normal or healthy subject; and
d. diagnosing the lymphoma based upon the level of the at least one protein in the plasma sample in comparison to the normal or healthy level.

16. A method of monitoring tumor response to treatment in a lymphoma patient, comprising:
a. obtaining a baseline plasma sample from the patient;
b. measuring the level of at least one protein listed in Table S3 in the baseline plasma sample;
c. administering therapy to the patient;
d. thereafter obtaining a second plasma sample from the patient;
e. measuring the level in the second plasma sample; and
f. comparing the levels; wherein a changed level after treatment indicates a therapeutic response.
